28TEST_F(DBBasicTestWithTimestamp, SanityChecks) {
29 Options options = CurrentOptions();
30 options.env = env_;
31 options.create_if_missing = true;
32 options.avoid_flush_during_shutdown = true;
33 options.merge_operator = MergeOperators::CreateStringAppendTESTOperator();
34 DestroyAndReopen(options);
35
36 Options options1 = CurrentOptions();
37 options1.env = env_;
38 options1.comparator = test::BytewiseComparatorWithU64TsWrapper();
39 options1.merge_operator = MergeOperators::CreateStringAppendTESTOperator();
40 assert(options1.comparator &&
41 options1.comparator->timestamp_size() == sizeof(uint64_t));
42 ColumnFamilyHandle* handle = nullptr;
43 Status s = db_->CreateColumnFamily(options1, "data", &handle);
44 ASSERT_OK(s);
45
46 std::string dummy_ts(sizeof(uint64_t), '\0');
47 // Perform timestamp operations on default cf.
48 ASSERT_TRUE(
49 db_->Put(WriteOptions(), "key", dummy_ts, "value").IsInvalidArgument());
50 ASSERT_TRUE(db_->Merge(WriteOptions(), db_->DefaultColumnFamily(), "key",
51 dummy_ts, "value")
52 .IsInvalidArgument());
53 ASSERT_TRUE(db_->Delete(WriteOptions(), "key", dummy_ts).IsInvalidArgument());
54 ASSERT_TRUE(
55 db_->SingleDelete(WriteOptions(), "key", dummy_ts).IsInvalidArgument());
56 ASSERT_TRUE(db_->DeleteRange(WriteOptions(), db_->DefaultColumnFamily(),
57 "begin_key", "end_key", dummy_ts)
58 .IsInvalidArgument());
59
60 // Perform non-timestamp operations on "data" cf.
61 ASSERT_TRUE(
62 db_->Put(WriteOptions(), handle, "key", "value").IsInvalidArgument());
63 ASSERT_TRUE(db_->Delete(WriteOptions(), handle, "key").IsInvalidArgument());
64 ASSERT_TRUE(
65 db_->SingleDelete(WriteOptions(), handle, "key").IsInvalidArgument());
66
67 ASSERT_TRUE(
68 db_->Merge(WriteOptions(), handle, "key", "value").IsInvalidArgument());
69 ASSERT_TRUE(db_->DeleteRange(WriteOptions(), handle, "begin_key", "end_key")
70 .IsInvalidArgument());
71
72 {
73 WriteBatch wb;
74 ASSERT_OK(wb.Put(handle, "key", "value"));
75 ASSERT_TRUE(db_->Write(WriteOptions(), &wb).IsInvalidArgument());
76 }
77 {
78 WriteBatch wb;
79 ASSERT_OK(wb.Delete(handle, "key"));
80 ASSERT_TRUE(db_->Write(WriteOptions(), &wb).IsInvalidArgument());
81 }
82 {
83 WriteBatch wb;
84 ASSERT_OK(wb.SingleDelete(handle, "key"));
85 ASSERT_TRUE(db_->Write(WriteOptions(), &wb).IsInvalidArgument());
86 }
87 {
88 WriteBatch wb;
89 ASSERT_OK(wb.DeleteRange(handle, "begin_key", "end_key"));
90 ASSERT_TRUE(db_->Write(WriteOptions(), &wb).IsInvalidArgument());
91 }
92
93 // Perform timestamp operations with timestamps of incorrect size.
94 const std::string wrong_ts(sizeof(uint32_t), '\0');
95 ASSERT_TRUE(db_->Put(WriteOptions(), handle, "key", wrong_ts, "value")
96 .IsInvalidArgument());
97 ASSERT_TRUE(db_->Merge(WriteOptions(), handle, "key", wrong_ts, "value")
98 .IsInvalidArgument());
99 ASSERT_TRUE(
100 db_->Delete(WriteOptions(), handle, "key", wrong_ts).IsInvalidArgument());
101 ASSERT_TRUE(db_->SingleDelete(WriteOptions(), handle, "key", wrong_ts)
102 .IsInvalidArgument());
103 ASSERT_TRUE(
104 db_->DeleteRange(WriteOptions(), handle, "begin_key", "end_key", wrong_ts)
105 .IsInvalidArgument());
106
107 delete handle;
108}

110TEST_F(DBBasicTestWithTimestamp, MixedCfs) {
111 Options options = CurrentOptions();
112 options.env = env_;
113 options.create_if_missing = true;
114 options.avoid_flush_during_shutdown = true;
115 DestroyAndReopen(options);
116
117 Options options1 = CurrentOptions();
118 options1.env = env_;
119 const size_t kTimestampSize = Timestamp(0, 0).size();
120 TestComparator test_cmp(kTimestampSize);
121 options1.comparator = &test_cmp;
122 ColumnFamilyHandle* handle = nullptr;
123 Status s = db_->CreateColumnFamily(options1, "data", &handle);
124 ASSERT_OK(s);
125
126 WriteBatch wb;
127 ASSERT_OK(wb.Put("a", "value"));
128 ASSERT_OK(wb.Put(handle, "a", "value"));
129 {
130 std::string ts = Timestamp(1, 0);
131 const auto ts_sz_func = [kTimestampSize, handle](uint32_t cf_id) {
132 assert(handle);
133 if (cf_id == 0) {
134 return static_cast<size_t>(0);
135 } else if (cf_id == handle->GetID()) {
136 return kTimestampSize;
137 } else {
138 assert(false);
139 return std::numeric_limits<size_t>::max();
140 }
141 };
142 ASSERT_OK(wb.UpdateTimestamps(ts, ts_sz_func));
143 ASSERT_OK(db_->Write(WriteOptions(), &wb));
144 }
145
146 const auto verify_db = [this](ColumnFamilyHandle* h, const std::string& key,
147 const std::string& ts,
148 const std::string& expected_value) {
149 ASSERT_EQ(expected_value, Get(key));
150 Slice read_ts_slice(ts);
151 ReadOptions read_opts;
152 read_opts.timestamp = &read_ts_slice;
153 std::string value;
154 ASSERT_OK(db_->Get(read_opts, h, key, &value));
155 ASSERT_EQ(expected_value, value);
156 };
157
158 verify_db(handle, "a", Timestamp(1, 0), "value");
159
160 delete handle;
161 Close();
162
163 std::vector<ColumnFamilyDescriptor> cf_descs;
164 cf_descs.emplace_back(kDefaultColumnFamilyName, options);
165 cf_descs.emplace_back("data", options1);
166 options.create_if_missing = false;
167 s = DB::Open(options, dbname_, cf_descs, &handles_, &db_);
168 ASSERT_OK(s);
169
170 verify_db(handles_[1], "a", Timestamp(1, 0), "value");
171
172 Close();
173}

175TEST_F(DBBasicTestWithTimestamp, MultiGetMultipleCfs) {
176 const size_t kTimestampSize = Timestamp(0, 0).size();
177 TestComparator test_cmp(kTimestampSize);
178 Options options = CurrentOptions();
179 options.env = env_;
180 options.create_if_missing = true;
181 options.avoid_flush_during_shutdown = true;
182 options.comparator = &test_cmp;
183 DestroyAndReopen(options);
184
185 Options options1 = CurrentOptions();
186 options1.env = env_;
187 options1.comparator = &test_cmp;
188 ColumnFamilyHandle* handle = nullptr;
189 Status s = db_->CreateColumnFamily(options1, "data", &handle);
190 ASSERT_OK(s);
191
192 std::string ts = Timestamp(1, 0);
193 WriteBatch wb(0, 0, 0, kTimestampSize);
194 ASSERT_OK(wb.Put("a", "value"));
195 ASSERT_OK(wb.Put(handle, "a", "value"));
196 const auto ts_sz_func = [kTimestampSize](uint32_t /*cf_id*/) {
197 return kTimestampSize;
198 };
199 ASSERT_OK(wb.UpdateTimestamps(ts, ts_sz_func));
200 ASSERT_OK(db_->Write(WriteOptions(), &wb));
201
202 int num_keys = 2;
203 std::vector<Slice> keys;
204 std::vector<std::string> expected_values;
205 for (int i = 0; i < num_keys; i++) {
206 keys.push_back("a");
207 expected_values.push_back("value");
208 }
209 std::vector<ColumnFamilyHandle*> handles;
210 handles.push_back(db_->DefaultColumnFamily());
211 handles.push_back(handle);
212
213 {
214 Slice read_ts_slice(ts);
215 ReadOptions read_opts;
216 read_opts.timestamp = &read_ts_slice;
217
218 std::vector<PinnableSlice> values;
219 values.resize(num_keys);
220 std::vector<Status> statuses;
221 statuses.resize(num_keys);
222 std::vector<std::string> timestamps;
223 timestamps.resize(num_keys);
224
225 db_->MultiGet(read_opts, num_keys, handles.data(), keys.data(),
226 values.data(), timestamps.data(), statuses.data());
227
228 for (int i = 0; i < num_keys; i++) {
229 ASSERT_OK(statuses[i]);
230 ASSERT_EQ(expected_values[i], values[i].ToString());
231 ASSERT_EQ(ts, timestamps[i]);
232 }
233 }
234
235 delete handle;
236 Close();
237}

265TEST_F(DBBasicTestWithTimestamp, GcPreserveLatestVersionBelowFullHistoryLow) {
266 Options options = CurrentOptions();
267 options.env = env_;
268 options.create_if_missing = true;
269 const size_t kTimestampSize = Timestamp(0, 0).size();
270 TestComparator test_cmp(kTimestampSize);
271 options.comparator = &test_cmp;
272 DestroyAndReopen(options);
273
274 std::string ts_str = Timestamp(1, 0);
275 WriteOptions wopts;
276 ASSERT_OK(db_->Put(wopts, "k1", ts_str, "v1"));
277 ASSERT_OK(db_->Put(wopts, "k2", ts_str, "v2"));
278 ASSERT_OK(db_->Put(wopts, "k3", ts_str, "v3"));
279
280 ts_str = Timestamp(2, 0);
281 ASSERT_OK(db_->Delete(wopts, "k3", ts_str));
282
283 ts_str = Timestamp(4, 0);
284 ASSERT_OK(db_->Put(wopts, "k1", ts_str, "v5"));
285
286 ts_str = Timestamp(5, 0);
287 ASSERT_OK(
288 db_->DeleteRange(wopts, db_->DefaultColumnFamily(), "k0", "k9", ts_str));
289
290 ts_str = Timestamp(3, 0);
291 Slice ts = ts_str;
292 CompactRangeOptions cro;
293 cro.full_history_ts_low = &ts;
294 ASSERT_OK(db_->CompactRange(cro, nullptr, nullptr));
295
296 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
297
298 ReadOptions ropts;
299 ropts.timestamp = &ts;
300 std::string value;
301 Status s = db_->Get(ropts, "k1", &value);
302 ASSERT_OK(s);
303 ASSERT_EQ("v1", value);
304
305 std::string key_ts;
306 ASSERT_TRUE(db_->Get(ropts, "k3", &value, &key_ts).IsNotFound());
307 ASSERT_EQ(Timestamp(2, 0), key_ts);
308
309 ts_str = Timestamp(5, 0);
310 ts = ts_str;
311 ropts.timestamp = &ts;
312 ASSERT_TRUE(db_->Get(ropts, "k2", &value, &key_ts).IsNotFound());
313 ASSERT_EQ(Timestamp(5, 0), key_ts);
314 ASSERT_TRUE(db_->Get(ropts, "k2", &value).IsNotFound());
315
316 Close();
317}

319TEST_F(DBBasicTestWithTimestamp, UpdateFullHistoryTsLow) {
320 Options options = CurrentOptions();
321 options.env = env_;
322 options.create_if_missing = true;
323 const size_t kTimestampSize = Timestamp(0, 0).size();
324 TestComparator test_cmp(kTimestampSize);
325 options.comparator = &test_cmp;
326 DestroyAndReopen(options);
327
328 const std::string kKey = "test kKey";
329
330 // Test set ts_low first and flush()
331 int current_ts_low = 5;
332 std::string ts_low_str = Timestamp(current_ts_low, 0);
333 Slice ts_low = ts_low_str;
334 CompactRangeOptions comp_opts;
335 comp_opts.full_history_ts_low = &ts_low;
336 comp_opts.bottommost_level_compaction = BottommostLevelCompaction::kForce;
337
338 ASSERT_OK(db_->CompactRange(comp_opts, nullptr, nullptr));
339
340 auto* cfd =
341 static_cast_with_check<ColumnFamilyHandleImpl>(db_->DefaultColumnFamily())
342 ->cfd();
343 auto result_ts_low = cfd->GetFullHistoryTsLow();
344
345 ASSERT_TRUE(test_cmp.CompareTimestamp(ts_low, result_ts_low) == 0);
346
347 for (int i = 0; i < 10; i++) {
348 WriteOptions write_opts;
349 std::string ts = Timestamp(i, 0);
350 ASSERT_OK(db_->Put(write_opts, kKey, ts, Key(i)));
351 }
352 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
353
354 for (int i = 0; i < 10; i++) {
355 ReadOptions read_opts;
356 std::string ts_str = Timestamp(i, 0);
357 Slice ts = ts_str;
358 read_opts.timestamp = &ts;
359 std::string value;
360 Status status = db_->Get(read_opts, kKey, &value);
361 if (i < current_ts_low) {
362 ASSERT_TRUE(status.IsInvalidArgument());
363 } else {
364 ASSERT_OK(status);
365 ASSERT_TRUE(value.compare(Key(i)) == 0);
366 }
367 }
368
369 // Test set ts_low and then trigger compaction
370 for (int i = 10; i < 20; i++) {
371 WriteOptions write_opts;
372 std::string ts = Timestamp(i, 0);
373 ASSERT_OK(db_->Put(write_opts, kKey, ts, Key(i)));
374 }
375
376 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
377
378 current_ts_low = 15;
379 ts_low_str = Timestamp(current_ts_low, 0);
380 ts_low = ts_low_str;
381 comp_opts.full_history_ts_low = &ts_low;
382 ASSERT_OK(db_->CompactRange(comp_opts, nullptr, nullptr));
383 result_ts_low = cfd->GetFullHistoryTsLow();
384 ASSERT_TRUE(test_cmp.CompareTimestamp(ts_low, result_ts_low) == 0);
385
386 for (int i = current_ts_low; i < 20; i++) {
387 ReadOptions read_opts;
388 std::string ts_str = Timestamp(i, 0);
389 Slice ts = ts_str;
390 read_opts.timestamp = &ts;
391 std::string value;
392 Status status = db_->Get(read_opts, kKey, &value);
393 ASSERT_OK(status);
394 ASSERT_TRUE(value.compare(Key(i)) == 0);
395 }
396
397 // Test invalid compaction with range
398 Slice start(kKey), end(kKey);
399 Status s = db_->CompactRange(comp_opts, &start, &end);
400 ASSERT_TRUE(s.IsInvalidArgument());
401 s = db_->CompactRange(comp_opts, &start, nullptr);
402 ASSERT_TRUE(s.IsInvalidArgument());
403 s = db_->CompactRange(comp_opts, nullptr, &end);
404 ASSERT_TRUE(s.IsInvalidArgument());
405
406 // Test invalid compaction with the decreasing ts_low
407 ts_low_str = Timestamp(current_ts_low - 1, 0);
408 ts_low = ts_low_str;
409 comp_opts.full_history_ts_low = &ts_low;
410 s = db_->CompactRange(comp_opts, nullptr, nullptr);
411 ASSERT_TRUE(s.IsInvalidArgument());
412
413 Close();
414}

416TEST_F(DBBasicTestWithTimestamp, UpdateFullHistoryTsLowWithPublicAPI) {
417 Options options = CurrentOptions();
418 options.env = env_;
419 options.create_if_missing = true;
420 const size_t kTimestampSize = Timestamp(0, 0).size();
421 TestComparator test_cmp(kTimestampSize);
422 options.comparator = &test_cmp;
423 DestroyAndReopen(options);
424 std::string ts_low_str = Timestamp(9, 0);
425 ASSERT_OK(
426 db_->IncreaseFullHistoryTsLow(db_->DefaultColumnFamily(), ts_low_str));
427 std::string result_ts_low;
428 ASSERT_OK(db_->GetFullHistoryTsLow(nullptr, &result_ts_low));
429 ASSERT_TRUE(test_cmp.CompareTimestamp(ts_low_str, result_ts_low) == 0);
430 // test increase full_history_low backward
431 std::string ts_low_str_back = Timestamp(8, 0);
432 auto s = db_->IncreaseFullHistoryTsLow(db_->DefaultColumnFamily(),
433 ts_low_str_back);
434 ASSERT_EQ(s, Status::InvalidArgument());
435 // test IncreaseFullHistoryTsLow with a timestamp whose length is longger
436 // than the cf's timestamp size
437 std::string ts_low_str_long(Timestamp(0, 0).size() + 1, 'a');
438 s = db_->IncreaseFullHistoryTsLow(db_->DefaultColumnFamily(),
439 ts_low_str_long);
440 ASSERT_EQ(s, Status::InvalidArgument());
441 // test IncreaseFullHistoryTsLow with a timestamp which is null
442 std::string ts_low_str_null;
443 s = db_->IncreaseFullHistoryTsLow(db_->DefaultColumnFamily(),
444 ts_low_str_null);
445 ASSERT_EQ(s, Status::InvalidArgument());
446 // test IncreaseFullHistoryTsLow for a column family that does not enable
447 // timestamp
448 options.comparator = BytewiseComparator();
449 DestroyAndReopen(options);
450 ts_low_str = Timestamp(10, 0);
451 s = db_->IncreaseFullHistoryTsLow(db_->DefaultColumnFamily(), ts_low_str);
452 ASSERT_EQ(s, Status::InvalidArgument());
453 // test GetFullHistoryTsLow for a column family that does not enable
454 // timestamp
455 std::string current_ts_low;
456 s = db_->GetFullHistoryTsLow(db_->DefaultColumnFamily(), &current_ts_low);
457 ASSERT_EQ(s, Status::InvalidArgument());
458 Close();
459}

461TEST_F(DBBasicTestWithTimestamp, GetApproximateSizes) {
462 Options options = CurrentOptions();
463 options.write_buffer_size = 100000000; // Large write buffer
464 options.compression = kNoCompression;
465 options.create_if_missing = true;
466 const size_t kTimestampSize = Timestamp(0, 0).size();
467 TestComparator test_cmp(kTimestampSize);
468 options.comparator = &test_cmp;
469 DestroyAndReopen(options);
470 auto default_cf = db_->DefaultColumnFamily();
471
472 WriteOptions write_opts;
473 std::string ts = Timestamp(1, 0);
474
475 const int N = 128;
476 Random rnd(301);
477 for (int i = 0; i < N; i++) {
478 ASSERT_OK(db_->Put(write_opts, Key(i), ts, rnd.RandomString(1024)));
479 }
480
481 uint64_t size;
482 std::string start = Key(50);
483 std::string end = Key(60);
484 Range r(start, end);
485 SizeApproximationOptions size_approx_options;
486 size_approx_options.include_memtables = true;
487 size_approx_options.include_files = true;
488 ASSERT_OK(
489 db_->GetApproximateSizes(size_approx_options, default_cf, &r, 1, &size));
490 ASSERT_GT(size, 6000);
491 ASSERT_LT(size, 204800);
492
493 // test multiple ranges
494 std::vector<Range> ranges;
495 std::string start_tmp = Key(10);
496 std::string end_tmp = Key(20);
497 ranges.emplace_back(start_tmp, end_tmp);
498 ranges.emplace_back(start, end);
499 uint64_t range_sizes[2];
500 ASSERT_OK(db_->GetApproximateSizes(size_approx_options, default_cf,
501 ranges.data(), 2, range_sizes));
502
503 ASSERT_EQ(range_sizes[1], size);
504
505 // Zero if not including mem table
506 ASSERT_OK(db_->GetApproximateSizes(&r, 1, &size));
507 ASSERT_EQ(size, 0);
508
509 start = Key(500);
510 end = Key(600);
511 r = Range(start, end);
512 ASSERT_OK(
513 db_->GetApproximateSizes(size_approx_options, default_cf, &r, 1, &size));
514 ASSERT_EQ(size, 0);
515
516 // Test range boundaries
517 ASSERT_OK(db_->Put(write_opts, Key(1000), ts, rnd.RandomString(1024)));
518 // Should include start key
519 start = Key(1000);
520 end = Key(1100);
521 r = Range(start, end);
522 ASSERT_OK(
523 db_->GetApproximateSizes(size_approx_options, default_cf, &r, 1, &size));
524 ASSERT_GT(size, 0);
525
526 uint64_t total_mem_count;
527 uint64_t total_mem_size;
528 db_->GetApproximateMemTableStats(default_cf, r, &total_mem_count,
529 &total_mem_size);
530 ASSERT_GT(total_mem_count, 0);
531 ASSERT_GT(total_mem_size, 0);
532
533 // Should exclude end key
534 start = Key(900);
535 end = Key(1000);
536 r = Range(start, end);
537 ASSERT_OK(
538 db_->GetApproximateSizes(size_approx_options, default_cf, &r, 1, &size));
539 ASSERT_EQ(size, 0);
540
541 Close();
542}

544TEST_F(DBBasicTestWithTimestamp, SimpleIterate) {
545 const int kNumKeysPerFile = 128;
546 const uint64_t kMaxKey = 1024;
547 Options options = CurrentOptions();
548 options.env = env_;
549 options.create_if_missing = true;
550 const size_t kTimestampSize = Timestamp(0, 0).size();
551 TestComparator test_cmp(kTimestampSize);
552 options.comparator = &test_cmp;
553 options.memtable_factory.reset(
554 test::NewSpecialSkipListFactory(kNumKeysPerFile));
555 DestroyAndReopen(options);
556 const std::vector<uint64_t> start_keys = {1, 0};
557 const std::vector<std::string> write_timestamps = {Timestamp(1, 0),
558 Timestamp(3, 0)};
559 const std::vector<std::string> read_timestamps = {Timestamp(2, 0),
560 Timestamp(4, 0)};
561 for (size_t i = 0; i < write_timestamps.size(); ++i) {
562 WriteOptions write_opts;
563 for (uint64_t key = start_keys[i]; key <= kMaxKey; ++key) {
564 Status s = db_->Put(write_opts, Key1(key), write_timestamps[i],
565 "value" + std::to_string(i));
566 ASSERT_OK(s);
567 }
568 }
569 for (size_t i = 0; i < read_timestamps.size(); ++i) {
570 ReadOptions read_opts;
571 Slice read_ts = read_timestamps[i];
572 read_opts.timestamp = &read_ts;
573 std::unique_ptr<Iterator> it(db_->NewIterator(read_opts));
574 int count = 0;
575 uint64_t key = 0;
576 // Forward iterate.
577 for (it->Seek(Key1(0)), key = start_keys[i]; it->Valid();
578 it->Next(), ++count, ++key) {
579 CheckIterUserEntry(it.get(), Key1(key), kTypeValue,
580 "value" + std::to_string(i), write_timestamps[i]);
581 }
582 size_t expected_count = kMaxKey - start_keys[i] + 1;
583 ASSERT_EQ(expected_count, count);
584
585 // Backward iterate.
586 count = 0;
587 for (it->SeekForPrev(Key1(kMaxKey)), key = kMaxKey; it->Valid();
588 it->Prev(), ++count, --key) {
589 CheckIterUserEntry(it.get(), Key1(key), kTypeValue,
590 "value" + std::to_string(i), write_timestamps[i]);
591 }
592 ASSERT_OK(it->status());
593 ASSERT_EQ(static_cast<size_t>(kMaxKey) - start_keys[i] + 1, count);
594
595 // SeekToFirst()/SeekToLast() with lower/upper bounds.
596 // Then iter with lower and upper bounds.
597 uint64_t l = 0;
598 uint64_t r = kMaxKey + 1;
599 while (l < r) {
600 std::string lb_str = Key1(l);
601 Slice lb = lb_str;
602 std::string ub_str = Key1(r);
603 Slice ub = ub_str;
604 read_opts.iterate_lower_bound = &lb;
605 read_opts.iterate_upper_bound = &ub;
606 it.reset(db_->NewIterator(read_opts));
607 for (it->SeekToFirst(), key = std::max(l, start_keys[i]), count = 0;
608 it->Valid(); it->Next(), ++key, ++count) {
609 CheckIterUserEntry(it.get(), Key1(key), kTypeValue,
610 "value" + std::to_string(i), write_timestamps[i]);
611 }
612 ASSERT_OK(it->status());
613 ASSERT_EQ(r - std::max(l, start_keys[i]), count);
614
615 for (it->SeekToLast(), key = std::min(r, kMaxKey + 1), count = 0;
616 it->Valid(); it->Prev(), --key, ++count) {
617 CheckIterUserEntry(it.get(), Key1(key - 1), kTypeValue,
618 "value" + std::to_string(i), write_timestamps[i]);
619 }
620 ASSERT_OK(it->status());
621 l += (kMaxKey / 100);
622 r -= (kMaxKey / 100);
623 }
624 }
625 Close();
626}

628TEST_F(DBBasicTestWithTimestamp, TrimHistoryTest) {
629 Options options = CurrentOptions();
630 options.env = env_;
631 options.create_if_missing = true;
632 const size_t kTimestampSize = Timestamp(0, 0).size();
633 TestComparator test_cmp(kTimestampSize);
634 options.comparator = &test_cmp;
635 DestroyAndReopen(options);
636 auto check_value_by_ts = [](DB* db, Slice key, std::string readTs,
637 Status status, std::string checkValue,
638 std::string expected_ts) {
639 ReadOptions ropts;
640 Slice ts = readTs;
641 ropts.timestamp = &ts;
642 std::string value;
643 std::string key_ts;
644 Status s = db->Get(ropts, key, &value, &key_ts);
645 ASSERT_TRUE(s == status);
646 if (s.ok()) {
647 ASSERT_EQ(checkValue, value);
648 }
649 if (s.ok() || s.IsNotFound()) {
650 ASSERT_EQ(expected_ts, key_ts);
651 }
652 };
653 // Construct data of different versions with different ts
654 ASSERT_OK(db_->Put(WriteOptions(), "k1", Timestamp(2, 0), "v1"));
655 ASSERT_OK(db_->Put(WriteOptions(), "k1", Timestamp(4, 0), "v2"));
656 ASSERT_OK(db_->Delete(WriteOptions(), "k1", Timestamp(5, 0)));
657 ASSERT_OK(db_->Put(WriteOptions(), "k1", Timestamp(6, 0), "v3"));
658 check_value_by_ts(db_, "k1", Timestamp(7, 0), Status::OK(), "v3",
659 Timestamp(6, 0));
660 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
661 Close();
662
663 ColumnFamilyOptions cf_options(options);
664 std::vector<ColumnFamilyDescriptor> column_families;
665 column_families.emplace_back(kDefaultColumnFamilyName, cf_options);
666 DBOptions db_options(options);
667
668 // Trim data whose version > Timestamp(5, 0), read(k1, ts(7)) <- NOT_FOUND.
669 ASSERT_OK(DB::OpenAndTrimHistory(db_options, dbname_, column_families,
670 &handles_, &db_, Timestamp(5, 0)));
671 check_value_by_ts(db_, "k1", Timestamp(7, 0), Status::NotFound(), "",
672 Timestamp(5, 0));
673 Close();
674
675 // Trim data whose timestamp > Timestamp(4, 0), read(k1, ts(7)) <- v2
676 ASSERT_OK(DB::OpenAndTrimHistory(db_options, dbname_, column_families,
677 &handles_, &db_, Timestamp(4, 0)));
678 check_value_by_ts(db_, "k1", Timestamp(7, 0), Status::OK(), "v2",
679 Timestamp(4, 0));
680 Close();
681
682 Reopen(options);
683 ASSERT_OK(db_->DeleteRange(WriteOptions(), db_->DefaultColumnFamily(), "k1",
684 "k3", Timestamp(7, 0)));
685 check_value_by_ts(db_, "k1", Timestamp(8, 0), Status::NotFound(), "",
686 Timestamp(7, 0));
687 Close();
688 // Trim data whose timestamp > Timestamp(6, 0), read(k1, ts(8)) <- v2
689 ASSERT_OK(DB::OpenAndTrimHistory(db_options, dbname_, column_families,
690 &handles_, &db_, Timestamp(6, 0)));
691 check_value_by_ts(db_, "k1", Timestamp(8, 0), Status::OK(), "v2",
692 Timestamp(4, 0));
693 Close();
694}

768 options.prefix_extractor.reset(NewFixedPrefixTransform(3));
769 options.compression = kNoCompression;
770 BlockBasedTableOptions bbto;
771 bbto.index_type = GetParam();
772 bbto.block_size = 100;
773 options.table_factory.reset(NewBlockBasedTableFactory(bbto));
774 const size_t kTimestampSize = Timestamp(0, 0).size();
775 TestComparator cmp(kTimestampSize);
776 options.comparator = &cmp;
777 DestroyAndReopen(options);
778 constexpr uint64_t kNumKeys = 1024;
779 for (uint64_t k = 0; k < kNumKeys; ++k) {
780 WriteOptions write_opts;
781 ASSERT_OK(db_->Put(write_opts, Key1(k), Timestamp(1, 0),
782 "value" + std::to_string(k)));
783 }

785 {

788 std::string ts_str = Timestamp(2, 0);
789 Slice ts = ts_str;
790 read_opts.timestamp = &ts;
791 std::unique_ptr<Iterator> it(db_->NewIterator(read_opts));
792 // verify Get()
793 for (it->SeekToFirst(); it->Valid(); it->Next()) {
794 std::string value_from_get;
795 std::string key_str(it->key().data(), it->key().size());
796 std::string timestamp;
797 ASSERT_OK(db_->Get(read_opts, key_str, &value_from_get, &timestamp));

802
803 // verify MultiGet()
804 constexpr uint64_t step = 2;
805 static_assert(0 == (kNumKeys % step),
806 "kNumKeys must be a multiple of step");
807 for (uint64_t k = 0; k < kNumKeys; k += 2) {
808 std::vector<std::string> key_strs;
809 std::vector<Slice> keys;
810 for (size_t i = 0; i < step; ++i) {
811 key_strs.push_back(Key1(k + i));
812 }
813 for (size_t i = 0; i < step; ++i) {
814 keys.emplace_back(key_strs[i]);
815 }
816 std::vector<std::string> values;
817 std::vector<std::string> timestamps;
818 std::vector<Status> statuses =
819 db_->MultiGet(read_opts, keys, &values, &timestamps);
820 ASSERT_EQ(step, statuses.size());
821 ASSERT_EQ(step, values.size());
822 ASSERT_EQ(step, timestamps.size());
823 for (uint64_t i = 0; i < step; ++i) {
824 ASSERT_OK(statuses[i]);
825 ASSERT_EQ("value" + std::to_string(k + i), values[i]);
826 ASSERT_EQ(Timestamp(1, 0), timestamps[i]);
827 }
828 }
829 }
830 Close();
831}

1005TEST_F(DBBasicTestWithTimestamp, ChangeIterationDirection) {
1006 Options options = GetDefaultOptions();
1007 options.create_if_missing = true;
1008 options.env = env_;
1009 const size_t kTimestampSize = Timestamp(0, 0).size();
1010 TestComparator test_cmp(kTimestampSize);
1011 options.comparator = &test_cmp;
1012 options.prefix_extractor.reset(NewFixedPrefixTransform(1));
1013 options.prefix_seek_opt_in_only = false; // Use legacy prefix seek
1014 options.statistics = ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::CreateDBStatistics();
1015 DestroyAndReopen(options);
1016 const std::vector<std::string> timestamps = {Timestamp(1, 1), Timestamp(0, 2),
1017 Timestamp(4, 3)};
1018 const std::vector<std::tuple<std::string, std::string>> kvs = {
1019 std::make_tuple("aa", "value1"), std::make_tuple("ab", "value2")};
1020 for (const auto& ts : timestamps) {
1021 WriteBatch wb(0, 0, 0, kTimestampSize);
1022 for (const auto& kv : kvs) {
1023 const std::string& key = std::get<0>(kv);
1024 const std::string& value = std::get<1>(kv);
1025 ASSERT_OK(wb.Put(key, value));
1026 }
1027
1028 ASSERT_OK(wb.UpdateTimestamps(
1029 ts, [kTimestampSize](uint32_t) { return kTimestampSize; }));
1030 ASSERT_OK(db_->Write(WriteOptions(), &wb));
1031 }
1032 std::string read_ts_str = Timestamp(5, 3);
1033 Slice read_ts = read_ts_str;
1034 ReadOptions read_opts;
1035 read_opts.timestamp = &read_ts;
1036 std::unique_ptr<Iterator> it(db_->NewIterator(read_opts));
1037
1038 it->SeekToFirst();
1039 ASSERT_TRUE(it->Valid());
1040 it->Prev();
1041 ASSERT_FALSE(it->Valid());
1042
1043 it->SeekToLast();
1044 ASSERT_TRUE(it->Valid());
1045 uint64_t prev_reseek_count =
1046 options.statistics->getTickerCount(NUMBER_OF_RESEEKS_IN_ITERATION);
1047 ASSERT_EQ(0, prev_reseek_count);
1048 it->Next();
1049 ASSERT_FALSE(it->Valid());
1050 ASSERT_EQ(1 + prev_reseek_count,
1051 options.statistics->getTickerCount(NUMBER_OF_RESEEKS_IN_ITERATION));
1052
1053 it->Seek(std::get<0>(kvs[0]));
1054 CheckIterUserEntry(it.get(), std::get<0>(kvs[0]), kTypeValue,
1055 std::get<1>(kvs[0]), Timestamp(4, 3));
1056 it->Next();
1057 CheckIterUserEntry(it.get(), std::get<0>(kvs[1]), kTypeValue,
1058 std::get<1>(kvs[1]), Timestamp(4, 3));
1059 it->Prev();
1060 CheckIterUserEntry(it.get(), std::get<0>(kvs[0]), kTypeValue,
1061 std::get<1>(kvs[0]), Timestamp(4, 3));
1062
1063 prev_reseek_count =
1064 options.statistics->getTickerCount(NUMBER_OF_RESEEKS_IN_ITERATION);
1065 ASSERT_EQ(1, prev_reseek_count);
1066 it->Next();
1067 CheckIterUserEntry(it.get(), std::get<0>(kvs[1]), kTypeValue,
1068 std::get<1>(kvs[1]), Timestamp(4, 3));
1069 ASSERT_EQ(1 + prev_reseek_count,
1070 options.statistics->getTickerCount(NUMBER_OF_RESEEKS_IN_ITERATION));
1071
1072 it->SeekForPrev(std::get<0>(kvs[1]));
1073 CheckIterUserEntry(it.get(), std::get<0>(kvs[1]), kTypeValue,
1074 std::get<1>(kvs[1]), Timestamp(4, 3));
1075 it->Prev();
1076 CheckIterUserEntry(it.get(), std::get<0>(kvs[0]), kTypeValue,
1077 std::get<1>(kvs[0]), Timestamp(4, 3));
1078
1079 prev_reseek_count =
1080 options.statistics->getTickerCount(NUMBER_OF_RESEEKS_IN_ITERATION);
1081 it->Next();
1082 CheckIterUserEntry(it.get(), std::get<0>(kvs[1]), kTypeValue,
1083 std::get<1>(kvs[1]), Timestamp(4, 3));
1084 ASSERT_EQ(1 + prev_reseek_count,
1085 options.statistics->getTickerCount(NUMBER_OF_RESEEKS_IN_ITERATION));
1086
1087 it.reset();
1088 Close();
1089}

1692TEST_F(DBBasicTestWithTimestamp, GetWithRowCache) {
1693 Options options = CurrentOptions();
1694 options.env = env_;
1695 options.create_if_missing = true;
1696 options.statistics = ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::CreateDBStatistics();
1697 LRUCacheOptions cache_options;
1698 cache_options.capacity = 8192;
1699 options.row_cache = cache_options.MakeSharedRowCache();
1700
1701 const size_t kTimestampSize = Timestamp(0, 0).size();
1702 TestComparator test_cmp(kTimestampSize);
1703 options.comparator = &test_cmp;
1704 DestroyAndReopen(options);
1705
1706 WriteOptions write_opts;
1707 std::string ts_early = Timestamp(1, 0);
1708 std::string ts_later = Timestamp(10, 0);
1709 Slice ts_later_slice = ts_later;
1710
1711 const Snapshot* snap_with_nothing = db_->GetSnapshot();
1712 ASSERT_OK(db_->Put(write_opts, "foo", ts_early, "bar"));
1713 ASSERT_OK(db_->Put(write_opts, "foo2", ts_early, "bar2"));
1714 ASSERT_OK(db_->Put(write_opts, "foo3", ts_early, "bar3"));
1715
1716 const Snapshot* snap_with_foo = db_->GetSnapshot();
1717 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
1718
1719 ReadOptions read_opts;
1720 read_opts.timestamp = &ts_later_slice;
1721
1722 std::string read_value;
1723 std::string read_ts;
1724 Status s;
1725
1726 int expected_hit_count = 0;
1727 int expected_miss_count = 0;
1728 ASSERT_EQ(TestGetTickerCount(options, ROW_CACHE_HIT), expected_hit_count);
1729 ASSERT_EQ(TestGetTickerCount(options, ROW_CACHE_MISS), expected_miss_count);
1730
1731 {
1732 read_opts.timestamp = nullptr;
1733 s = db_->Get(read_opts, "foo", &read_value);
1734 ASSERT_NOK(s);
1735 ASSERT_TRUE(s.IsInvalidArgument());
1736 }
1737
1738 // Mix use of Get
1739 {
1740 read_opts.timestamp = &ts_later_slice;
1741
1742 // Use Get without ts first, expect cache entry to store the correct ts
1743 s = db_->Get(read_opts, "foo2", &read_value);
1744 ASSERT_OK(s);
1745 ASSERT_EQ(TestGetTickerCount(options, ROW_CACHE_HIT), expected_hit_count);
1746 ASSERT_EQ(TestGetTickerCount(options, ROW_CACHE_MISS),
1747 ++expected_miss_count);
1748 ASSERT_EQ(read_value, "bar2");
1749
1750 s = db_->Get(read_opts, "foo2", &read_value, &read_ts);
1751 ASSERT_OK(s);
1752 ASSERT_EQ(TestGetTickerCount(options, ROW_CACHE_HIT), ++expected_hit_count);
1753 ASSERT_EQ(TestGetTickerCount(options, ROW_CACHE_MISS), expected_miss_count);
1754 ASSERT_EQ(read_ts, ts_early);
1755 ASSERT_EQ(read_value, "bar2");
1756
1757 // Use Get with ts first, expect the Get without ts can get correct record
1758 s = db_->Get(read_opts, "foo3", &read_value, &read_ts);
1759 ASSERT_OK(s);
1760 ASSERT_EQ(TestGetTickerCount(options, ROW_CACHE_HIT), expected_hit_count);
1761 ASSERT_EQ(TestGetTickerCount(options, ROW_CACHE_MISS),
1762 ++expected_miss_count);
1763 ASSERT_EQ(read_ts, ts_early);
1764 ASSERT_EQ(read_value, "bar3");
1765
1766 s = db_->Get(read_opts, "foo3", &read_value);
1767 ASSERT_OK(s);
1768 ASSERT_EQ(TestGetTickerCount(options, ROW_CACHE_HIT), ++expected_hit_count);
1769 ASSERT_EQ(TestGetTickerCount(options, ROW_CACHE_MISS), expected_miss_count);
1770 ASSERT_EQ(read_value, "bar3");
1771 }
1772
1773 {
1774 // Test with consecutive calls of Get with ts.
1775 s = db_->Get(read_opts, "foo", &read_value, &read_ts);
1776 ASSERT_OK(s);
1777 ASSERT_EQ(TestGetTickerCount(options, ROW_CACHE_HIT), expected_hit_count);
1778 ASSERT_EQ(TestGetTickerCount(options, ROW_CACHE_MISS),
1779 ++expected_miss_count);

2859TEST_P(DBBasicTestWithTimestampCompressionSettings, PutDeleteGet) {
2860 Options options = CurrentOptions();
2861 options.env = env_;
2862 options.create_if_missing = true;
2863 const size_t kTimestampSize = Timestamp(0, 0).size();
2864 TestComparator test_cmp(kTimestampSize);
2865 options.comparator = &test_cmp;
2866 const int kNumKeysPerFile = 1024;
2867 options.memtable_factory.reset(
2868 test::NewSpecialSkipListFactory(kNumKeysPerFile));
2869 BlockBasedTableOptions bbto;
2870 bbto.filter_policy = std::get<0>(GetParam());
2871 bbto.whole_key_filtering = true;
2872 options.table_factory.reset(NewBlockBasedTableFactory(bbto));
2873
2874 const CompressionType comp_type = std::get<1>(GetParam());
2875#if LZ4_VERSION_NUMBER < 10400 // r124+
2876 if (comp_type == kLZ4Compression || comp_type == kLZ4HCCompression) {
2877 return;
2878 }
2879#endif // LZ4_VERSION_NUMBER >= 10400
2880 if (!ZSTD_Supported() && comp_type == kZSTD) {
2881 return;
2882 }
2883 if (!Zlib_Supported() && comp_type == kZlibCompression) {
2884 return;
2885 }
2886
2887 options.compression = comp_type;
2888 options.compression_opts.max_dict_bytes = std::get<2>(GetParam());
2889 if (comp_type == kZSTD) {
2890 options.compression_opts.zstd_max_train_bytes = std::get<2>(GetParam());
2891 }
2892 options.compression_opts.parallel_threads = std::get<3>(GetParam());
2893 options.target_file_size_base = 1 << 26; // 64MB
2894
2895 DestroyAndReopen(options);
2896
2897 const size_t kNumL0Files =
2898 static_cast<size_t>(Options().level0_file_num_compaction_trigger);
2899 {
2900 // Half of the keys will go through Deletion and remaining half with
2901 // SingleDeletion. Generate enough L0 files with ts=1 to trigger compaction
2902 // to L1
2903 std::string ts = Timestamp(1, 0);
2904 WriteOptions wopts;
2905 for (size_t i = 0; i < kNumL0Files; ++i) {
2906 for (int j = 0; j < kNumKeysPerFile; ++j) {
2907 ASSERT_OK(db_->Put(wopts, Key1(j), ts, "value" + std::to_string(i)));
2908 }
2909 ASSERT_OK(db_->Flush(FlushOptions()));
2910 }
2911 ASSERT_OK(dbfull()->TEST_WaitForCompact());
2912 // Generate another L0 at ts=3
2913 ts = Timestamp(3, 0);
2914 for (int i = 0; i < kNumKeysPerFile; ++i) {
2915 std::string key_str = Key1(i);
2916 Slice key(key_str);
2917 if ((i % 3) == 0) {
2918 if (i < kNumKeysPerFile / 2) {
2919 ASSERT_OK(db_->Delete(wopts, key, ts));
2920 } else {
2921 ASSERT_OK(db_->SingleDelete(wopts, key, ts));
2922 }
2923 } else {
2924 ASSERT_OK(db_->Put(wopts, key, ts, "new_value"));
2925 }
2926 }
2927 ASSERT_OK(db_->Flush(FlushOptions()));
2928 // Populate memtable at ts=5
2929 ts = Timestamp(5, 0);
2930 for (int i = 0; i != kNumKeysPerFile; ++i) {
2931 std::string key_str = Key1(i);
2932 Slice key(key_str);
2933 if ((i % 3) == 1) {
2934 if (i < kNumKeysPerFile / 2) {
2935 ASSERT_OK(db_->Delete(wopts, key, ts));
2936 } else {
2937 ASSERT_OK(db_->SingleDelete(wopts, key, ts));
2938 }
2939 } else if ((i % 3) == 2) {
2940 ASSERT_OK(db_->Put(wopts, key, ts, "new_value_2"));
2941 }
2942 }
2943 }
2944 {
2945 std::string ts_str = Timestamp(6, 0);
2946 Slice ts = ts_str;
2947 ReadOptions ropts;
2948 ropts.timestamp = &ts;
2949 for (uint64_t i = 0; i != static_cast<uint64_t>(kNumKeysPerFile); ++i) {
2950 std::string value;
2951 std::string key_ts;
2952 Status s = db_->Get(ropts, Key1(i), &value, &key_ts);
2953 if ((i % 3) == 2) {
2954 ASSERT_OK(s);
2955 ASSERT_EQ("new_value_2", value);
2956 ASSERT_EQ(Timestamp(5, 0), key_ts);
2957 } else if ((i % 3) == 1) {
2958 ASSERT_TRUE(s.IsNotFound());
2959 ASSERT_EQ(Timestamp(5, 0), key_ts);
2960 } else {
2961 ASSERT_TRUE(s.IsNotFound());
2962 ASSERT_EQ(Timestamp(3, 0), key_ts);
2963 }
2964 }
2965 }

3283TEST_P(DBBasicTestWithTimestampPrefixSeek, IterateWithPrefix) {
3284 const size_t kNumKeysPerFile = 128;
3285 Options options = CurrentOptions();
3286 options.env = env_;
3287 options.create_if_missing = true;
3288 const size_t kTimestampSize = Timestamp(0, 0).size();
3289 TestComparator test_cmp(kTimestampSize);
3290 options.comparator = &test_cmp;
3291 options.prefix_extractor = std::get<0>(GetParam());
3292 options.memtable_factory.reset(
3293 test::NewSpecialSkipListFactory(kNumKeysPerFile));
3294 BlockBasedTableOptions bbto;
3295 bbto.filter_policy = std::get<1>(GetParam());
3296 bbto.index_type = std::get<3>(GetParam());
3297 options.table_factory.reset(NewBlockBasedTableFactory(bbto));
3298 DestroyAndReopen(options);
3299
3300 const uint64_t kMaxKey = 0xffffffffffffffff;
3301 const uint64_t kMinKey = 0xfffffffffffff000;
3302 const std::vector<std::string> write_ts_list = {Timestamp(3, 0xffffffff),
3303 Timestamp(6, 0xffffffff)};
3304 WriteOptions write_opts;
3305 {
3306 for (size_t i = 0; i != write_ts_list.size(); ++i) {
3307 for (uint64_t key = kMaxKey; key >= kMinKey; --key) {
3308 Status s = db_->Put(write_opts, Key1(key), write_ts_list[i],
3309 "value" + std::to_string(i));
3310 ASSERT_OK(s);
3311 }
3312 }
3313 }
3314 const std::vector<std::string> read_ts_list = {Timestamp(5, 0xffffffff),
3315 Timestamp(9, 0xffffffff)};
3316 {
3317 ReadOptions read_opts;
3318 read_opts.total_order_seek = false;
3319 read_opts.prefix_same_as_start = std::get<2>(GetParam());
3320 fprintf(stdout, "%s %s %d\n", options.prefix_extractor->Name(),
3321 bbto.filter_policy ? bbto.filter_policy->Name() : "null",
3322 static_cast<int>(read_opts.prefix_same_as_start));
3323 for (size_t i = 0; i != read_ts_list.size(); ++i) {
3324 Slice read_ts = read_ts_list[i];
3325 read_opts.timestamp = &read_ts;
3326 std::unique_ptr<Iterator> iter(db_->NewIterator(read_opts));
3327
3328 // Seek to kMaxKey
3329 iter->Seek(Key1(kMaxKey));
3330 CheckIterUserEntry(iter.get(), Key1(kMaxKey), kTypeValue,
3331 "value" + std::to_string(i), write_ts_list[i]);
3332 iter->Next();
3333 ASSERT_FALSE(iter->Valid());
3334 ASSERT_OK(iter->status());
3335
3336 // Seek to kMinKey
3337 iter->Seek(Key1(kMinKey));
3338 CheckIterUserEntry(iter.get(), Key1(kMinKey), kTypeValue,
3339 "value" + std::to_string(i), write_ts_list[i]);
3340 iter->Prev();
3341 ASSERT_FALSE(iter->Valid());
3342 ASSERT_OK(iter->status());
3343 }
3344 const std::vector<uint64_t> targets = {kMinKey, kMinKey + 0x10,
3345 kMinKey + 0x100, kMaxKey};
3346 const SliceTransform* const pe = options.prefix_extractor.get();
3347 ASSERT_NE(nullptr, pe);
3348 const size_t kPrefixShift =
3349 8 * (Key1(0).size() - pe->Transform(Key1(0)).size());
3350 const uint64_t kPrefixMask =
3351 ~((static_cast<uint64_t>(1) << kPrefixShift) - 1);
3352 const uint64_t kNumKeysWithinPrefix =
3353 (static_cast<uint64_t>(1) << kPrefixShift);
3354 for (size_t i = 0; i != read_ts_list.size(); ++i) {
3355 Slice read_ts = read_ts_list[i];
3356 read_opts.timestamp = &read_ts;
3357 std::unique_ptr<Iterator> it(db_->NewIterator(read_opts));
3358 // Forward and backward iterate.
3359 for (size_t j = 0; j != targets.size(); ++j) {
3360 std::string start_key = Key1(targets[j]);
3361 uint64_t expected_ub =
3362 (targets[j] & kPrefixMask) - 1 + kNumKeysWithinPrefix;
3363 uint64_t expected_key = targets[j];
3364 size_t count = 0;
3365 it->Seek(Key1(targets[j]));
3366 while (it->Valid()) {
3367 std::string saved_prev_key;
3368 saved_prev_key.assign(it->key().data(), it->key().size());
3369
3370 // Out of prefix
3371 if (!read_opts.prefix_same_as_start &&
3372 pe->Transform(saved_prev_key) != pe->Transform(start_key)) {
3373 break;
3374 }
3375 CheckIterUserEntry(it.get(), Key1(expected_key), kTypeValue,
3376 "value" + std::to_string(i), write_ts_list[i]);
3377 ++count;
3378 ++expected_key;
3379 it->Next();
3380 }
3381 ASSERT_OK(it->status());
3382 ASSERT_EQ(expected_ub - targets[j] + 1, count);
3383
3384 count = 0;
3385 expected_key = targets[j];
3386 it->SeekForPrev(start_key);
3387 uint64_t expected_lb = (targets[j] & kPrefixMask);
3388 while (it->Valid()) {
3389 // Out of prefix
3390 if (!read_opts.prefix_same_as_start &&
3391 pe->Transform(it->key()) != pe->Transform(start_key)) {
3392 break;
3393 }
3394 CheckIterUserEntry(it.get(), Key1(expected_key), kTypeValue,
3395 "value" + std::to_string(i), write_ts_list[i]);
3396 ++count;
3397 --expected_key;
3398 it->Prev();
3399 }
3400 ASSERT_OK(it->status());
3401 ASSERT_EQ(targets[j] - std::max(expected_lb, kMinKey) + 1, count);
3402 }
3403 }
3404 }
3405 Close();
3406}

3535};

3537TEST_F(UpdateFullHistoryTsLowTest, ConcurrentUpdate) {
3538 Options options = CurrentOptions();
3539 options.env = env_;
3540 options.create_if_missing = true;
3541 std::string lower_ts_low = Timestamp(10, 0);
3542 std::string higher_ts_low = Timestamp(25, 0);
3543 const size_t kTimestampSize = lower_ts_low.size();
3544 TestComparator test_cmp(kTimestampSize);
3545 options.comparator = &test_cmp;
3546
3547 DestroyAndReopen(options);
3548 SyncPoint::GetInstance()->DisableProcessing();
3549 SyncPoint::GetInstance()->ClearAllCallBacks();
3550 // This workaround swaps `lower_ts_low` originally used for update by the
3551 // caller to `higher_ts_low` after its writer is queued to make sure
3552 // the caller will always get a TryAgain error.
3553 // It mimics cases where two threads update full_history_ts_low concurrently
3554 // with one thread writing a higher ts_low and one thread writing a lower
3555 // ts_low.
3556 VersionEdit* version_edit;
3557 SyncPoint::GetInstance()->SetCallBack(
3558 "DBImpl::IncreaseFullHistoryTsLowImpl:BeforeEdit",
3559 [&](void* arg) { version_edit = static_cast<VersionEdit*>(arg); });
3560 SyncPoint::GetInstance()->SetCallBack(
3561 "VersionSet::LogAndApply:BeforeWriterWaiting",
3562 [&](void* /*arg*/) { version_edit->SetFullHistoryTsLow(higher_ts_low); });
3563 SyncPoint::GetInstance()->EnableProcessing();
3564 ASSERT_TRUE(
3565 db_->IncreaseFullHistoryTsLow(db_->DefaultColumnFamily(), lower_ts_low)
3566 .IsTryAgain());
3567 SyncPoint::GetInstance()->DisableProcessing();
3568 SyncPoint::GetInstance()->ClearAllCallBacks();
3569
3570 Close();
3571}

3602
3603 ASSERT_OK(

3764// Tests that as long as the
3765// `ReadOptions.timestamp >= SuperVersion.full_history_ts_low` sanity check
3766// passes. The read will be consistent even if the column family's
3767// full_history_ts_low is concurrently increased and collapsed some history
3768// above `ReadOptions.timestamp`.
3769TEST_F(DBBasicTestWithTimestamp,
3770 FullHistoryTsLowSanityCheckPassReadIsConsistent) {
3771 Options options = CurrentOptions();
3772 options.env = env_;
3773 options.comparator = test::BytewiseComparatorWithU64TsWrapper();
3774 // Use UDT in memtable only feature for this test, so we can control that
3775 // newly set `full_history_ts_low` collapse history when Flush happens.
3776 options.persist_user_defined_timestamps = false;
3777 options.allow_concurrent_memtable_write = false;
3778 DestroyAndReopen(options);
3779 std::string min_ts;
3780 PutFixed64(&min_ts, 0);
3781
3782 // Write two versions of the key (1, v1), (3, v3), and always read with
3783 // timestamp 2.
3784 std::string write_ts;
3785 PutFixed64(&write_ts, 1);
3786 ASSERT_OK(db_->Put(WriteOptions(), "foo", write_ts, "val1"));
3787
3788 std::string read_ts;
3789 PutFixed64(&read_ts, 2);
3790 Slice read_ts_slice = read_ts;
3791 ReadOptions read_opts;
3792 read_opts.timestamp = &read_ts_slice;
3793
3794 // First read, no full_history_ts_low set, sanity check pass.
3795 std::string value;
3796 std::string timestamp;
3797 ASSERT_OK(db_->Get(read_opts, "foo", &value, &timestamp));
3798 ASSERT_EQ("val1", value);
3799 ASSERT_EQ(write_ts, timestamp);
3800
3801 std::string full_history_ts_low;
3802 std::string marked_ts_low;
3803 PutFixed64(&full_history_ts_low, 2);
3804 marked_ts_low = full_history_ts_low;
3805 ASSERT_OK(db_->IncreaseFullHistoryTsLow(db_->DefaultColumnFamily(),
3806 full_history_ts_low));
3807 ASSERT_OK(Flush(0));
3808
3809 // Write the (3, v3) entry after flush, otherwise with UDT in memtable only
3810 // the previous Flush(0) with full_history_ts_low = 2 will be postponed
3811 // waiting for (3, v3) to expire too.
3812 write_ts.clear();
3813 PutFixed64(&write_ts, 3);
3814 ASSERT_OK(db_->Put(WriteOptions(), "foo", write_ts, "val3"));
3815
3816 // Second read:
3817 // ReadOptions.timestamp(2) >= SuperVersion.full_history_ts_low(2),
3818 // and ReadOptions.timestamp(2) >= ColumnFamilyData.full_history_ts_low(2).
3819 // history below 2 is collapsed. Reading at 2 or above 2 is ok.
3820 // Sanity check pass. Read return consistent value, but timestamp is already
3821 // collapsed.
3822 ASSERT_OK(db_->Get(read_opts, "foo", &value, &timestamp));
3823 ASSERT_EQ("val1", value);
3824 ASSERT_EQ(min_ts, timestamp);
3825
3826 SyncPoint::GetInstance()->SetCallBack(
3827 "DBImpl::GetImpl:AfterAcquireSv", [&](void* /*arg*/) {
3828 // Concurrently increasing full_history_ts_low and flush to create a
3829 // new SuperVersion
3830 std::string current_ts_low;
3831 ASSERT_OK(db_->GetFullHistoryTsLow(db_->DefaultColumnFamily(),
3832 &current_ts_low));
3833 if (current_ts_low.empty() || current_ts_low != marked_ts_low) {
3834 return;
3835 }
3836 full_history_ts_low.clear();
3837 PutFixed64(&full_history_ts_low, 4);
3838 ASSERT_OK(db_->IncreaseFullHistoryTsLow(db_->DefaultColumnFamily(),
3839 full_history_ts_low));
3840 ASSERT_OK(Flush(0));
3841 });
3842
3843 SyncPoint::GetInstance()->EnableProcessing();
3844
3845 // Third read:
3846 // ReadOptions.timestamp(2) >= SuperVersion.full_history_ts_low(2),
3847 // but ReadOptions.timestamp(2) < ColumnFamilyData.full_history_ts_low(4).
3848 // History below 4 is collapsed in the newly installed SuperVersion. But the
3849 // SuperVersion attached to this read still has the history below 4 available.
3850 // Sanity check pass. Read return consistent value, timestamp is collapsed.
3851 ASSERT_OK(db_->Get(read_opts, "foo", &value, &timestamp));
3852 ASSERT_EQ("val1", value);
3853 ASSERT_EQ(min_ts, timestamp);
3854
3855 // Fourth read:
3856 // ReadOptions.timestamp(2) < SuperVersion.full_history_ts_low(4).
3857 // Sanity check fails. Had it succeeded, the read would return "v3",
3858 // which is inconsistent.
3859 ASSERT_TRUE(
3860 db_->Get(read_opts, "foo", &value, &timestamp).IsInvalidArgument());
3861 Close();
3862
3863 SyncPoint::GetInstance()->DisableProcessing();
3864 SyncPoint::GetInstance()->ClearAllCallBacks();
3865}

4080 values.data(), timestamps.data(), statuses.data(),

4082 ASSERT_TRUE(statuses[0].IsNotFound());
4083 ASSERT_EQ(timestamps[0], Timestamp(3, 0));
4084 ASSERT_TRUE(statuses[1].IsNotFound());
4085 // DeleteRange has a higher timestamp than Delete for "k2"
4086 ASSERT_EQ(timestamps[1], Timestamp(3, 0));
4087 ASSERT_OK(statuses[2]);
4088 ASSERT_EQ(values[2], "v3");
4089 ASSERT_EQ(timestamps[2], Timestamp(4, 0));
4090
4091 CompactRangeOptions cro;
4092 // Range tombstone has timestamp >= full_history_ts_low, covered keys
4093 // are not dropped.
4094 std::string compaction_ts_str = Timestamp(2, 0);
4095 Slice compaction_ts = compaction_ts_str;
4096 cro.full_history_ts_low = &compaction_ts;
4097 cro.bottommost_level_compaction = BottommostLevelCompaction::kForce;
4098 ASSERT_OK(db_->CompactRange(cro, nullptr, nullptr));
4099 ropts.timestamp = &compaction_ts;
4100 std::string value, ts;
4101 ASSERT_OK(db_->Get(ropts, "k1", &value, &ts));
4102 ASSERT_EQ(value, "v1");
4103 // timestamp is below full_history_ts_low, zeroed out as the key goes into
4104 // bottommost level
4105 ASSERT_EQ(ts, Timestamp(0, 0));
4106 ASSERT_TRUE(db_->Get(ropts, "k2", &value, &ts).IsNotFound());
4107 ASSERT_EQ(ts, Timestamp(2, 0));
4108
4109 compaction_ts_str = Timestamp(4, 0);
4110 compaction_ts = compaction_ts_str;
4111 cro.full_history_ts_low = &compaction_ts;
4112 ASSERT_OK(db_->CompactRange(cro, nullptr, nullptr));
4113 ropts.timestamp = &read_ts_slice;
4114 // k1, k2 and the range tombstone should be dropped
4115 // k3 should still exist
4116 db_->MultiGet(ropts, db_->DefaultColumnFamily(), batch_size, keys.data(),
4117 values.data(), timestamps.data(), statuses.data(),
4118 true /* sorted_input */);
4119 ASSERT_TRUE(statuses[0].IsNotFound());
4120 ASSERT_TRUE(timestamps[0].empty());
4121 ASSERT_TRUE(statuses[1].IsNotFound());
4122 ASSERT_TRUE(timestamps[1].empty());
4123 ASSERT_OK(statuses[2]);
4124 ASSERT_EQ(values[2], "v3");
4125 ASSERT_EQ(timestamps[2], Timestamp(4, 0));
4126
4127 Close();
4128}

4153TEST_P(DeleteRangeWithTimestampTableOptions, BasicReadAndIterate) {

4155 Options options = CurrentOptions();
4156 options.disable_auto_compactions = true;
4157 options.prefix_extractor.reset(NewFixedPrefixTransform(3));
4158 options.compression = kNoCompression;
4159 BlockBasedTableOptions bbto;
4160 bbto.index_type = std::get<0>(GetParam());
4161 bbto.block_size = 100;
4162 options.table_factory.reset(NewBlockBasedTableFactory(bbto));
4163 options.env = env_;
4164 options.create_if_missing = true;
4165 bool persist_udt = test::ShouldPersistUDT(std::get<1>(GetParam()));
4166 options.comparator = test::BytewiseComparatorWithU64TsWrapper();
4167 options.persist_user_defined_timestamps = persist_udt;
4168 // UDT in memtables only not compatible with concurrent memtable writes.
4169 options.allow_concurrent_memtable_write = persist_udt;
4170 options.memtable_factory.reset(test::NewSpecialSkipListFactory(kNumPerFile));
4171 DestroyAndReopen(options);
4172
4173 // Write half of the keys before the tombstone and half after the tombstone.
4174 // Only covered keys (i.e., within the range and older than the tombstone)
4175 // should be deleted.
4176 std::string full_history_ts_low;

4180 PutFixed64(&write_ts, i);
4181 if (i == kNum / 2) {
4182 ASSERT_OK(db_->DeleteRange(WriteOptions(), db_->DefaultColumnFamily(),
4183 Key1(kRangeBegin), Key1(kRangeEnd), write_ts));
4184 }
4185 ASSERT_OK(
4186 db_->Put(WriteOptions(), Key1(i), write_ts, "val" + std::to_string(i)));
4187 if (i == kNum - kNumPerFile) {
4188 if (!persist_udt) {
4189 // When UDTs are not persisted, mark the timestamps in the Memtables as
4190 // all expired so the followed flush can go through.
4191 cutoff_ts = i + 1;
4192 PutFixed64(&full_history_ts_low, cutoff_ts);
4193 ASSERT_OK(db_->IncreaseFullHistoryTsLow(db_->DefaultColumnFamily(),
4194 full_history_ts_low));
4195 }
4196 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
4197 }
4198 }
4199
4200 ReadOptions read_opts;
4201 read_opts.total_order_seek = true;
4202 std::string read_ts;
4203 PutFixed64(&read_ts, kNum);
4204 Slice read_ts_slice = read_ts;
4205 read_opts.timestamp = &read_ts_slice;
4206 {
4207 std::unique_ptr<Iterator> iter(db_->NewIterator(read_opts));
4208 ASSERT_OK(iter->status());
4209
4210 int expected = 0;
4211 for (iter->SeekToFirst(); iter->Valid(); iter->Next()) {
4212 ASSERT_EQ(Key1(expected), iter->key());
4213 if (expected == kRangeBegin - 1) {
4214 expected = kNum / 2;
4215 } else {
4216 ++expected;
4217 }
4218 }
4219 ASSERT_OK(iter->status());
4220 ASSERT_EQ(kNum, expected);
4221
4222 expected = kNum / 2;
4223 for (iter->Seek(Key1(kNum / 2)); iter->Valid(); iter->Next()) {
4224 ASSERT_EQ(Key1(expected), iter->key());
4225 ++expected;
4226 }
4227 ASSERT_OK(iter->status());
4228 ASSERT_EQ(kNum, expected);
4229
4230 expected = kRangeBegin - 1;
4231 for (iter->SeekForPrev(Key1(kNum / 2 - 1)); iter->Valid(); iter->Prev()) {
4232 ASSERT_EQ(Key1(expected), iter->key());
4233 --expected;
4234 }
4235 ASSERT_OK(iter->status());
4236 ASSERT_EQ(-1, expected);
4237
4238 // Cannot read below the cutoff timestamp when timestamps are not persisted.
4239 if (persist_udt) {
4240 read_ts.clear();
4241 PutFixed64(&read_ts, 0);
4242 read_ts_slice = read_ts;
4243 read_opts.timestamp = &read_ts_slice;
4244 iter.reset(db_->NewIterator(read_opts));
4245 iter->SeekToFirst();
4246 ASSERT_TRUE(iter->Valid());
4247 ASSERT_EQ(iter->key(), Key1(0));
4248 iter->Next();
4249 ASSERT_FALSE(iter->Valid());
4250 ASSERT_OK(iter->status());
4251 }
4252 }
4253
4254 read_ts.clear();
4255 PutFixed64(&read_ts, kNum);
4256 read_ts_slice = read_ts;
4257 read_opts.timestamp = &read_ts_slice;
4258 std::string value, timestamp;
4259 Status s;
4260 std::string expected_ts;
4261 int int_expected_ts;
4262 for (int i = 0; i < kNum; ++i) {
4263 s = db_->Get(read_opts, Key1(i), &value, &timestamp);
4264 if (i >= kRangeBegin && i < kNum / 2) {
4265 ASSERT_TRUE(s.IsNotFound());
4266 int_expected_ts = (persist_udt || kNum / 2 >= cutoff_ts) ? kNum / 2 : 0;
4267 } else {
4268 ASSERT_OK(s);
4269 ASSERT_EQ(value, "val" + std::to_string(i));
4270 int_expected_ts = (persist_udt || i >= cutoff_ts) ? i : 0;
4271 }
4272 expected_ts.clear();
4273 PutFixed64(&expected_ts, int_expected_ts);
4274 ASSERT_EQ(timestamp, expected_ts);
4275 }
4276
4277 size_t batch_size = kNum;
4278 std::vector<std::string> key_strs(batch_size);
4279 std::vector<Slice> keys(batch_size);
4280 std::vector<PinnableSlice> values(batch_size);
4281 std::vector<Status> statuses(batch_size);
4282 std::vector<std::string> timestamps(batch_size);
4283 for (int i = 0; i < kNum; ++i) {
4284 key_strs[i] = Key1(i);
4285 keys[i] = key_strs[i];
4286 }
4287 db_->MultiGet(read_opts, db_->DefaultColumnFamily(), batch_size, keys.data(),
4288 values.data(), timestamps.data(), statuses.data(),
4289 true /* sorted_input */);
4290 for (int i = 0; i < kNum; ++i) {
4291 if (i >= kRangeBegin && i < kNum / 2) {
4292 ASSERT_TRUE(statuses[i].IsNotFound());
4293 int_expected_ts = (persist_udt || kNum / 2 >= cutoff_ts) ? kNum / 2 : 0;
4294 } else {
4295 ASSERT_OK(statuses[i]);
4296 ASSERT_EQ(values[i], "val" + std::to_string(i));
4297 int_expected_ts = (persist_udt || i >= cutoff_ts) ? i : 0;

4299 expected_ts.clear();
4300 PutFixed64(&expected_ts, int_expected_ts);
4301 ASSERT_EQ(timestamps[i], expected_ts);
4302 }
4303
4304 CompactRangeOptions cro;
4305 cro.bottommost_level_compaction = BottommostLevelCompaction::kForce;
4306 if (!persist_udt) {
4307 // Mark everything expired so manual compaction can go through
4308 full_history_ts_low.clear();
4309 PutFixed64(&full_history_ts_low, kNum);
4310 ASSERT_OK(db_->IncreaseFullHistoryTsLow(db_->DefaultColumnFamily(),
4311 full_history_ts_low));
4312 }
4313 Slice compaction_ts = full_history_ts_low;
4314 cro.full_history_ts_low = &compaction_ts;
4315 ASSERT_OK(db_->CompactRange(cro, nullptr, nullptr));
4316 for (int i = kRangeBegin; i < kNum / 2; ++i) {
4317 s = db_->Get(read_opts, Key1(i), &value, &timestamp);
4318 ASSERT_TRUE(s.IsNotFound());

4322 ASSERT_EQ(timestamp, expected_ts);
4323 } else {
4324 // When timestamps are not persisted, data in SST files all logically have
4325 // min timestamp. A compaction to the last level will drop the range

4327 ASSERT_TRUE(timestamp.empty());
4328 }
4329 }

4587TEST_F(DBBasicTestWithTimestamp, MergeAfterDeletion) {
4588 Options options = GetDefaultOptions();
4589 options.create_if_missing = true;
4590 const size_t kTimestampSize = Timestamp(0, 0).size();
4591 TestComparator test_cmp(kTimestampSize);
4592 options.comparator = &test_cmp;
4593 options.merge_operator = std::make_shared<StringAppendTESTOperator>('.');
4594 DestroyAndReopen(options);
4595
4596 ColumnFamilyHandle* const column_family = db_->DefaultColumnFamily();
4597
4598 const size_t num_keys_per_file = 10;
4599 const size_t num_merges_per_key = 2;
4600 for (size_t i = 0; i < num_keys_per_file; ++i) {
4601 std::string ts = Timestamp(i + 10000, 0);
4602 Status s = db_->Delete(WriteOptions(), Key1(i), ts);
4603 ASSERT_OK(s);
4604 for (size_t j = 1; j <= num_merges_per_key; ++j) {
4605 ts = Timestamp(i + 10000 + j, 0);
4606 s = db_->Merge(WriteOptions(), column_family, Key1(i), ts,
4607 std::to_string(j));
4608 ASSERT_OK(s);
4609 }
4610 }
4611
4612 const auto verify_db = [&]() {
4613 ReadOptions read_opts;
4614 std::string read_ts_str = Timestamp(20000, 0);
4615 Slice ts = read_ts_str;
4616 read_opts.timestamp = &ts;
4617 std::unique_ptr<Iterator> it(db_->NewIterator(read_opts));
4618 size_t count = 0;
4619 for (it->SeekToFirst(); it->Valid(); it->Next(), ++count) {
4620 std::string key = Key1(count);
4621 ASSERT_EQ(key, it->key());
4622 std::string value;
4623 for (size_t j = 1; j <= num_merges_per_key; ++j) {
4624 value.append(std::to_string(j));
4625 if (j < num_merges_per_key) {
4626 value.push_back('.');
4627 }
4628 }
4629 ASSERT_EQ(value, it->value());
4630 std::string ts1 = Timestamp(count + 10000 + num_merges_per_key, 0);
4631 ASSERT_EQ(ts1, it->timestamp());
4632 }
4633 ASSERT_OK(it->status());
4634 ASSERT_EQ(num_keys_per_file, count);
4635 for (it->SeekToLast(); it->Valid(); it->Prev(), --count) {
4636 std::string key = Key1(count - 1);
4637 ASSERT_EQ(key, it->key());
4638 std::string value;

4712TEST_F(DBBasicTestWithTimestamp, TimestampFilterTableReadOnGet) {
4713 Options options = CurrentOptions();
4714 options.env = env_;
4715 options.create_if_missing = true;
4716 options.statistics = ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::CreateDBStatistics();
4717 const size_t kTimestampSize = Timestamp(0, 0).size();
4718 TestComparator test_cmp(kTimestampSize);
4719 options.comparator = &test_cmp;
4720 BlockBasedTableOptions bbto;
4721 bbto.block_size = 100;
4722 options.table_factory.reset(NewBlockBasedTableFactory(bbto));
4723 DestroyAndReopen(options);
4724
4725 // Put
4726 // Create two SST files
4727 // file1: key => [1, 3], timestamp => [10, 20]
4728 // file2, key => [2, 4], timestamp => [30, 40]
4729 {
4730 WriteOptions write_opts;
4731 std::string write_ts = Timestamp(10, 0);
4732 ASSERT_OK(db_->Put(write_opts, Key1(1), write_ts, "value1"));
4733 write_ts = Timestamp(20, 0);
4734 ASSERT_OK(db_->Put(write_opts, Key1(3), write_ts, "value3"));
4735 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
4736
4737 write_ts = Timestamp(30, 0);
4738 ASSERT_OK(db_->Put(write_opts, Key1(2), write_ts, "value2"));
4739 write_ts = Timestamp(40, 0);
4740 ASSERT_OK(db_->Put(write_opts, Key1(4), write_ts, "value4"));
4741 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
4742 }
4743
4744 // Get with timestamp
4745 {
4746 auto prev_checked_events = options.statistics->getTickerCount(
4747 Tickers::TIMESTAMP_FILTER_TABLE_CHECKED);
4748 auto prev_filtered_events = options.statistics->getTickerCount(
4749 Tickers::TIMESTAMP_FILTER_TABLE_FILTERED);
4750
4751 // key=3 (ts=20) does not exist at timestamp=1
4752 std::string read_ts_str = Timestamp(1, 0);
4753 Slice read_ts_slice = Slice(read_ts_str);
4754 ReadOptions read_opts;
4755 read_opts.timestamp = &read_ts_slice;
4756 std::string value_from_get;
4757 std::string timestamp_from_get;
4758 auto status =
4759 db_->Get(read_opts, Key1(3), &value_from_get, &timestamp_from_get);
4760 ASSERT_TRUE(status.IsNotFound());
4761 ASSERT_EQ(value_from_get, std::string(""));
4762 ASSERT_EQ(timestamp_from_get, std::string(""));
4763
4764 // key=3 is in the key ranges for both files, so both files will be queried.
4765 // The table read was skipped because the timestamp is out of the table
4766 // range, i.e.., 1 < [10,20], [30,40].
4767 // The tickers increase by 2 due to 2 files.
4768 ASSERT_EQ(prev_checked_events + 2,
4769 options.statistics->getTickerCount(
4770 Tickers::TIMESTAMP_FILTER_TABLE_CHECKED));
4771 ASSERT_EQ(prev_filtered_events + 2,
4772 options.statistics->getTickerCount(
4773 Tickers::TIMESTAMP_FILTER_TABLE_FILTERED));
4774
4775 // key=3 (ts=20) exists at timestamp = 25
4776 read_ts_str = Timestamp(25, 0);
4777 read_ts_slice = Slice(read_ts_str);
4778 read_opts.timestamp = &read_ts_slice;
4779 ASSERT_OK(
4780 db_->Get(read_opts, Key1(3), &value_from_get, &timestamp_from_get));
4781 ASSERT_EQ("value3", value_from_get);
4782 ASSERT_EQ(Timestamp(20, 0), timestamp_from_get);
4783
4784 // file1 was not skipped, because the timestamp is in range, [10,20] < 25.
4785 // file2 was skipped, because the timestamp is not in range, 25 < [30,40].
4786 // So the checked ticker increase by 2 due to 2 files;
4787 // filtered ticker increase by 1 because file2 was skipped
4788 ASSERT_EQ(prev_checked_events + 4,
4789 options.statistics->getTickerCount(
4790 Tickers::TIMESTAMP_FILTER_TABLE_CHECKED));
4791 ASSERT_EQ(prev_filtered_events + 3,
4792 options.statistics->getTickerCount(
4793 Tickers::TIMESTAMP_FILTER_TABLE_FILTERED));
4794 }
4795
4796 Close();
4797}
